                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits/5217: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-29T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 29, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:57 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178. Your circular telegram January 24, 4 p.m.<note n="74" xml:id="d143fn74">Not
                        printed; it requested information as to what control measures had been
                        instituted (840.51 Frozen Credits/5168a).</note> No freezing control
                    measures have been instituted. Chilean Government was informed my note December
                    19 that we would like to see prompt adoption measures numbered 1, 3, 4 and 5 of
                    Department’s telegram December 15, 10 p.m.,<note n="75" xml:id="d143fn75">Not
                        printed; in this telegram the Department expressed the desire that the
                        American Republics prevent or curb business transactions with the Axis and
                        indicated the measures desirable to freeze the business operations of
                        individuals, banks and other companies having Axis connections (840.51
                        Frozen Credits/4686a).</note> but so far as can be learned here no action in
                    this connection is contemplated at this juncture.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
